Information about arguments used in actions/goals/smem reps


## Objects

^argument
  ^arg-type object
  ^arg-status 
    real - The object is a real object in the world
    abstract - The object is a description and shouldn't be matched against the world
  ^id <obj> - The object representation, usually on the world

^argument
  ^arg-type predicate
    ^arg-status
      real - The predicate should already exist in the world
      desired - The predicate should be achieved during the action
      abstract - The predicate is a description and is only for internal use


